						<div class="postbody">Is there any real reason why PAL Controllers are so impossible to find for sale, and when they are, they're like $40-50?  On any given day, I can find 20 pages of US controllers for $10-15ish in good condition on Ebay, same with the SFC version, but only like 1 or 2 listings for PAL ones (and yes, I'm searching worldwide).  Is there maybe a better place to find them?  Of the 3 designs (JPN/USA/PAL), the PAL version is my favorite, as it has the multi-colored buttons like the SFC, but it has the 6-foot cable and says Super Nintendo instead of Super Famicom.  Also, the Super Nintendo logo is dark and bold instead of the light and faded color on the USA version.  But yeah, I'm not paying $50 + shipping for a controller.</div>

